<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Fake News Detection Report</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg: #0f172a;
            --bg-soft: #111827;
            --card: #1e293b;
            --card-2: #243447;
            --text: #e5eef9;
            --muted: #94a3b8;
            --accent: #38bdf8;
            --accent-2: #f97316;
            --accent-3: #22c55e;
            --danger: #ef4444;
            --border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
            --shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
        }

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: "Segoe UI", Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background:
                radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.15), transparent 30%),
                radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.12), transparent 25%),
                linear-gradient(135deg, #0b1120, #0f172a 35%, #111827 100%);
            color: var(--text);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .container {
            width: min(1200px, 92%);
            margin: 40px auto;
        }

        .hero {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.16), rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.16));
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 22px;
            padding: 32px;
            margin-bottom: 28px;
            box-shadow: var(--shadow);
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
        }

        .hero h1 {
            margin: 0 0 10px;
            font-size: 2.4rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.4px;
        }

        .hero p {
            margin: 0;
            color: var(--muted);
            font-size: 1.05rem;
        }

        .metric-row {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
            gap: 18px;
            margin: 24px 0 30px;
        }

        .metric-card {
            background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.03), rgba(255,255,255,0.01));
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 18px;
            padding: 22px;
            box-shadow: var(--shadow);
        }

        .metric-label {
            color: var(--muted);
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .metric-value {
            font-size: 2rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: var(--accent);
        }

        .section {
            background: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.88);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 20px;
            padding: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 24px;
            box-shadow: var(--shadow);
        }

        .section h2 {
            margin-top: 0;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
            font-size: 1.45rem;
            color: #ffffff;
        }

        .section p {
            color: var(--muted);
            margin-top: 0;
        }

        .chart-wrapper {
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 16px;
            padding: 18px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .chart-wrapper img {
            max-width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            border-radius: 12px;
        }

        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin-top: 12px;
            overflow: hidden;
            border-radius: 14px;
        }

        th {
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.22), rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.22));
            color: #ffffff;
            font-weight: 600;
            text-align: left;
            padding: 14px 12px;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }

        td {
            padding: 12px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            vertical-align: top;
            color: #e2e8f0;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        tr:nth-child(even) td {
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
        }

        tr:hover td {
            background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.08);
            transition: 0.2s ease;
        }

        .grid-two {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 22px;
        }

        .grid-one {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            gap: 22px;
        }

        .badge {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 6px 12px;
            border-radius: 999px;
            background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.15);
            color: #86efac;
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.25);
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            color: var(--muted);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            padding: 20px 0 10px;
        }

        @media (max-width: 900px) {
            .grid-two {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }

            .hero h1 {
                font-size: 1.9rem;
            }

            .metric-value {
                font-size: 1.7rem;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">

        <section class="hero">
            <h1>Fake News Detection Report</h1>
            <p>Automated classification report generated from the dataset analysis, text vectorization, model training, and evaluation pipeline.</p>
            <div class="badge">Machine Learning Report</div>
        </section>

        <section class="metric-row">
            <div class="metric-card">
                <div class="metric-label">Model Accuracy</div>
                <div class="metric-value">{{ accuracy }}%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-card">
                <div class="metric-label">Main Task</div>
                <div class="metric-value" style="color: var(--accent-2); font-size: 1.4rem;">FAKE vs REAL</div>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-card">
                <div class="metric-label">Pipeline</div>
                <div class="metric-value" style="color: var(--accent-3); font-size: 1.2rem;">TF-IDF + SGD</div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>News Distribution</h2>
            <p>This chart shows the balance between fake and real news entries in the dataset.</p>
            <div class="chart-wrapper">
                <img src="{{ chart_path }}" alt="News distribution graph">
            </div>
        </section>

        <div class="grid-two">
            <section class="section">
                <h2>Confusion Matrix</h2>
                <p>Rows represent actual labels and columns represent predicted labels.</p>
                {{ confusion_table | safe }}
            </section>

            <section class="section">
                <h2>Error Summary</h2>
                <p>This table summarizes the types of classification errors made by the model.</p>
                {{ error_summary_table | safe }}
            </section>
        </div>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Classification Report</h2>
            <p>Precision, recall, f1-score, and support for each class.</p>
            {{ report_table | safe }}
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Misclassified Samples</h2>
            <p>Examples of texts where the model prediction did not match the real label, including score and confidence.</p>
            {{ misclassified_table | safe }}
        </section>

        <div class="grid-two">
            <section class="section">
                <h2>Correctly Classified FAKE News</h2>
                <p>Examples of fake news articles correctly identified by the model.</p>
                {{ correct_fake_table | safe }}
            </section>

            <section class="section">
                <h2>Correctly Classified REAL News</h2>
                <p>Examples of real news articles correctly identified by the model.</p>
                {{ correct_real_table | safe }}
            </section>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            Generated automatically with Python, pandas, scikit-learn, matplotlib, and Jinja2.
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>